President Obama has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key administration posts. Huban A. Gowadia will be appointed as the Director for Domestic Nuclear Detection at the Department of Homeland Security. Geoffrey L. Haskett will be appointed as the United States Commissioner for the U.S.-Russia Polar Bear Commission, and Gary Frazer will be appointed as the United States Alternate Commissioner for the same commission. Additionally, Douglas Frantz will be appointed as the Assistant Secretary for Public Affairs at the Department of State. President Obama believes that these individuals bring valuable experience and dedication to their new roles and looks forward to working with them in the future.